name: ATV Broadcast Studies Spurts
description:
Fine Art Gicleé Print.

Extra smooth acid free, 100% cotton 300gsm Muso Portfolio Rag. Printed by Image Science in Melbourne.

Signed and embossed by Eamon Donnelly.

Available in Landscape.

Australian Television (ATV) Broadcast Studies Number 1.

This is a study of how a medium can transcend it’s original purpose and journey through many conversions. Content originally shot for TV on film, broadcast live to air on Australian Commercial Television, illegally taped on personal home video recorders onto analog magnetic tape in the form of VHS and Beta, discarded with the onset of DVD, rediscovered via various recycling outlets 30 years later, collected, converted and archived into a digital format, broadcast again in 2012 through RCA cabling from DVD onto a 1988 Phillips Natural 14″ CRT Tube Television, stills then taken using digital photography and broadcast as static images online with no context to their original commercial purpose.

name: Studies in Broadcast Colour 5
description:
Fine Art Gicleé Print.

Extra smooth acid free, 100% cotton 300gsm Muso Portfolio Rag. Printed by Image Science in Melbourne. 
Signed and embossed by Eamon Donnelly.

Available in Portrait, Landscape or Square.

Studies in Broadcast Colour’ by The Island Continent is an exploration into the way colour is rendered and translated through the red, green and blue channels of obsolete Cathode Ray Tube or CRT television sets. Taken using modern digital SLR photography of a static colour broadcast via a 1988 Phillips Natural 14″ CRT Tube Television, this is part of an ongoing series of colour, moving image and archival television studies magnified through the RGB CRT screen.
